	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I think the big problem is that most raids take up too much time and dedication for a game.<br />
<br />
For example when I was getting flagged, I had to plan my real life time around EQ time.  It should be the other way around.  I had to make sure I did not get stuck at work late or I would miss the flag.<br />
<br />
I would bet most casual players would love to raid if it did not take 3-6 hours a night and require an average of 4-6 nights a week<br />
<br />
Most raids are boring as hell...2-3 hours of killing yard trash..then the named..there are exceptions of course.</font></p>
	
