	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Thecklos </i><br />
Even raider vs non raider, there wouldn't be any reason at all to play the raid game if the loot wasn't different for some people.  For others yeah we like to raid.  <hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
I think the point of the non-raider is, "What is our incentive to play?"    The difference between what the best equipped non-raider can do and what the best equipped raider can do is immense.   I wouldnt mind seeing uber loot drops that only have full stats when you are in a raid with at least 36 people.<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>But does it even fit in a RPG (online, pen and paper or otherwise) for the easiest mobs to drop loot that is just as good as the hardest mobs?  Come on....<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Hard is relative.   Define what is hard for one group and then drop loot that is appropriate to the challenge.   With instancing, that is easily done.    Raiders do pay a price for being raiders; they have to be a drone in a large guild, they have to play alot to reap rewards, they have to participate in a DKP system that makes the game more work than play.   Should that be reward?  I dont know, I guess so.   However, raiding should not give you the best loot PLUS the best experience spots, plus the best 1-group droppable loot, plus the best tradeskill drops, etc...<br />
<br />
[quoteI still think they should revise loot in places like NToV so that its at least better than LDoN hard droppable items.[/quote]<br />
<br />
They need to change all 5-7 day spawns to 3 day, make all 3 day spawns 1 day, and make all 1 day spawns 8 hours.   They need to add a mid level LDON mission level between normal and hard.  They need to retune LDON raids to be doable by 12-18 people and make the more rewarding based on the total LDON wins of the players. <br />
<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>Single group content should not be better than raid content, even if it is 3 group raid content. <hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Maybe not a single encounter, but a series of such challenges should.<br />
<br />
Bleh, having the same silly debate on the Monk boards.</font></p>
	
