	Location: Lansing, Michigan<br>
	Posts: 139</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Denec </i><br />
<b>I would bet most casual players would love to raid if it did not take 3-6 hours a night and require an average of 4-6 nights a week</b><hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Don't we do this to ourselves?  The only restriction in regards to this the game has is named respawn times.  Isn't it guilds who make folks raid so many hours and so many days?  I know things like VT and Time runs take quite a while, but why not play for 3 hours a night and than log, what you didn't get to hopefully you'll get to next time.<br />
<br />
I personally think a lot of the raiding players have already left.  Casual players join raiding guilds because they are now recruiting maybe?  Suddenly the casual player is walking in the shoes of the raiding player who they are replacing, the player is still casual but the raiding guild has rules.<br />
<br />
I also don't quite get the idea of raiding just to see the content.  There are tons of games on the shelves of my local computer store, those products are just like GoD and OoW.  Don't buy them and than complain about feeling *required* to play them.<br />
<br />
With the PoP release SoE painted EQ into the corner of having a raiding end game.  I think it was a bad decision and what has lead to discouraged casual players.  <br />
<br />
The only potential solution I see is an expansion like Velious or Luclin, where 90% of the zones are accessible without the need of a trial or key, and folks can enjoy all the zones without the need to be in a raid guild, even if it means they only kill one mob every 5 minutes.  Even this might not work though if the drops are not some content between the highest end raiding and LDoN purchases.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Kloven Knightowl<br />
Archon of Tunare<br />
Freedom Guard, Povar</font></p></p>
