	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>No, people should not be able to attain the same gear through easier paths (like it or not, group content is easier than raid content, you've given many reasons why it is easier when you state why you don't like it).<hr></blockquote> <br />
I agree with that.  A mob that <i>requires</i> 30-50+ people should always drop loot much better than stuff that only requires 6 people.  It takes a lot more people to bring that guy down, so the loot needs to be worth it.  I don't have a problem with raiders getting much better loot.  Not at all, in fact that's one of the larger incentives to raid, IMO (other being access to high end zones in the expansion).<br />
<br />
The only thing I have a problem with is the lack of significant upgrades for non-raiders.<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>If you don't like raiding but you do enjoy playing the game, then there is a lot of content to do with single groups. If you've actually done all of that consider a new character.<hr></blockquote> <br />
Call me crazy, but isn't that a lot like saying "we'd rather give the raiders more stuff to do than non-raiders"?  Just how much single-group content is there for 65 non-raiders outside of repetitive and monotonous LDoN adventures that has a meaningful and significant upgrade? (I don't mean single-groupable by elemental-geared with 300 AAs)  And out of that list, how many aren't heavily contested by raiders and farmers as well?<br />
<br />
You never hear the devs telling raiders that if they've done it all, they should play a different character.</font></p>
	
