	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b>Re: Couple of things</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>First off making gear have different stats when you were in a raid vs not in a raid would lead to things like "raid grinds" where people joined the raid with their group and then went to a separate part of the zone to grind in such that nobody was close enough to another group to actually shrare experience (sort of like what necros did for a while in gropus of 6 necros for the exp bonus.)<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
If they were going to exclude new ideas because some players would try to exploit it, EQ could be shipped on a 360k floppy.  Though I think more likely to happen is people would have 2 sets of gear, which is really not a good answer ether.  I hated have a seperate set of resist gear and bought an EB aug from LDON because I am too lazy to switch out an EB item.<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>Second off, if you actually read very much of that thread there are people that refuse to group with more than 5-11 other people max period.  I'm sorry to say, but iI just don't and can't feel sorry for somebody over drops that isn't even willing to try 18-24man content.  I'm not saying that large scale 72 man raiding is the end all of the game, but some of these people seem to want the same loots found in potime off quarm to drop off things that are 3 mannable because they think they deserve it and that it's unfair if they can't have it.<br />
<br />
I find that whole attitude wrong, life is more like a sewer....What you get out of it depends on what you put into it.<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Im sure there are people that extreme.   What I would like to see the default progression path be designed for the skilled and dedicated player to advance without having to joining a guild.  The whole guild concept was added as a social mechanism and the /raid tool wasnt added till Luclin expansion (?).   That highlights the fact that raiding guilds were a accomdation to the environment that SOE has tended to favor and not a principle foundation of the game as first envisioned.</font></p>
	
